-- GSK chooses Philip Hampton as next chairman
-- By Ben Hirschler
-- Thu Sep 25, 2014 03:10AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Sept 25 (Reuters) - GlaxoSmithKline <GSK.L> said on Thursday it had chosen Philip Hampton, who currently chairs Royal Bank of Scotland <RBS.L>, as its next chairman.

He will join the board in January and will become chairman with effect from Sept. 1, 2015, or at an earlier date if released from other commitments.